        <body>
            <div type="acto" n="1">
                <div type="escena" n="3">
                    <head>
                        <supplied>1.3</supplied>
                    </head>
                    <stage xml:lang="eng" xml:id="g4n2k7m9q1_eng" corresp="#g4n2k7m9q1_spa">Enter Laertes, and Ophelia 
                    <app>
                    <lem>his sister.</lem>
                    <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-absent"></rdg>
                    </app>
                    </stage>
                    <stage xml:lang="spa" xml:id="g4n2k7m9q1_spa" corresp="#g4n2k7m9q1_eng">[Entra Laertes y su hermana Ofelia]</stage>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="p7c3l9x2e8_eng" corresp="#p7c3l9x2e8_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>My necessaries are inbarked. Farewell.</l>
                        <l>And sister, as the winds give benefit</l>
                        <l>And convey is assistant, do not sleep</l>
                        <l>But let me hear from you.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="p7c3l9x2e8_spa" corresp="#p7c3l9x2e8_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Mis pertenencias están a bordo. Hasta pronto.</l>
                        <l>Y hermana, mientras el viento sea bueno</l>
                        <l>Y nos otroge su ayuda, no duermas</l>
                        <l>Mas déjame saber de ti.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="m8v4j1z6r3_eng" corresp="#m8v4j1z6r3_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>Do you doubt that?</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="m8v4j1z6r3_spa" corresp="#m8v4j1z6r3_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>¿Acaso lo dudas?</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="s2f9d5h3k8_eng" corresp="#s2f9d5h3k8_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>For Hamlet, and the trifling of his 
                        <app>
                        <lem>favor</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#F1" >favours</rdg>
                        </app>
                        ,</l>
                        <l>Hold it a fashion and a toy in blood,</l>
                        <l>A violet in the youth of primy nature,</l>
                        <l>Forward, not permanent, sweet, not lasting,</l>
                        <l>The
                            <app>
                            <lem>perfume and</lem> 
                            <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-absent"></rdg>
                            </app>
                            
                            suppliance of a minute,</l>
                        <l>No more.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="s2f9d5h3k8_spa" corresp="#s2f9d5h3k8_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Por Hamlet, y la insignificancia de su favor,</l>
                        <l>Tómalo como capricho e impulso carnal,</l>
                        <l>Una violeta en la juventud de la naturaleza primaria,</l>
                        <l>Continuo, no permanente, dulce, no duradero,</l>
                        <l>El perfume y el placer efímero,</l>
                        <l>Nada más.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="q5k8m2z9v4_eng" corresp="#q5k8m2z9v4_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>No more but so
                        <app>
                        <lem>?</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-orthography">.</rdg>
                        </app>
                    </l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="q5k8m2z9v4_spa" corresp="#q5k8m2z9v4_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>¿Nada más y aún así?</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="h3d7s1c9b2_eng" corresp="#h3d7s1c9b2_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Think it no more.</l>
                        <l>For nature crescent does not grow alone</l>
                        <l>In thews and bulks, but as this temple waxes</l>
                        <l>The inward service of the mind and soul</l>
                        <l>Grows wide withal. Perhaps he loves you now,</l>
                        <l>And now no soil nor cautel doth 
                        <app>
                        <lem>besmirch</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#F1">besmereh</rdg>
                        </app></l>
                        <l>The virtue of his 
                            <app>
                            <lem>will</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">feare</rdg>
                            </app>
                            ; but you must fear,</l>
                        <l>His greatness weighed, his will is not his own...
                            <app>
                            <lem n="..."></lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-present">For hee himselfe is subieet to his Birth:</rdg>
                            </app></l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="h3d7s1c9b2_spa" corresp="#h3d7s1c9b2_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>No lo pienses más.</l>
                        <l>Pues la naturaleza, que crece en fuerza y tamaño,</l>
                        <l>al crecer este templo, crece también</l>
                        <l>el servicio interior de la mente y del alma.</l>
                        <l>Quizás te ame ahora,</l>
                        <l>y nada manche la virtud de su voluntad;</l>
                        <l>pero debes temer:</l>
                        <l>su grandeza medida, su querer no es suyo...</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="r9t3b6k2m8_eng" corresp="#r9t3b6k2m8_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>He may not, as unvalued persons do,</l>
                        <l>Carve for himself, for on his choice depends</l>
                        <l>The 
                        <app>
                        <lem>safety</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#F1">sanetity</rdg>
                        </app> 
                        and health of this whole state,</l>
                        <l>And therefore must his choice be circumscribed</l>
                        <l>Unto the voice and yielding of that body</l>
                        <l>Whereof he is the head. Then if he says he loves you,</l>
                        <l>It fits your wisdom so far to believe it</l>
                        <l>As he in his particular 
                            <app>
                            <lem>act and place</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">Seet and foree</rdg>
                            </app></l>
                        <l>May give his saying deed, which is no further</l>
                        <l>Than the main voice of Denmark goes withal.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="r9t3b6k2m8_spa" corresp="#r9t3b6k2m8_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>No puede, como los hombres sin rango,</l>
                        <l>forjarse su propio destino, pues de su elección</l>
                        <l>depende la salud y seguridad de todo el estado;</l>
                        <l>y por eso su querer debe limitarse</l>
                        <l>a la voz y al consentimiento de aquel cuerpo</l>
                        <l>cuyo jefe es. Si entonces dice amarte,</l>
                        <l>conviene a tu prudencia creerlo</l>
                        <l>solo hasta donde sus actos lo confirmen,</l>
                        <l>y eso no más allá de lo que el pueblo de Dinamarca apruebe.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="k4v9d2m7x3_eng" corresp="#k4v9d2m7x3_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Then weigh what loss your honor may sustain</l>
                        <l>If with too credent ear you list his songs,</l>
                        <l>Or lose your heart, or your chaste treasure open</l>
                        <l>To his unmastered importunity.</l>
                        <l>Fear it, Ophelia, fear it, my dear sister,</l>
                        <l>And keep 
                            <app>
                            <lem>you in the rear</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">within the reare</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            of your affection,</l>
                        <l>Out of the shot and danger of desire.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="k4v9d2m7x3_spa" corresp="#k4v9d2m7x3_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Piensa, entonces, qué pérdida sufriría tu honor</l>
                        <l>si con oído crédulo escuchas sus cantos,</l>
                        <l>si pierdes tu corazón, o tu tesoro casto abres</l>
                        <l>a su importunidad indómita.</l>
                        <l>Teme, Ofelia, teme, mi querida hermana,</l>
                        <l>y mantén a raya tu afecto,</l>
                        <l>fuera del alcance y peligro del deseo.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="b7n5q3x8r4_eng" corresp="#b7n5q3x8r4_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>The chariest maid is prodigal enough</l>
                        <l>If she unmask her beauty to the moon.</l>
                        <l>Virtue itself scapes not calumnious strokes.</l>
                        <l>The canker galls the infants of the spring</l>
                        <l>Too oft before 
                            <app>
                            <lem>their</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">the</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            buttons be disclosed,</l>
                        <l>And in the morn and liquid dew of youth</l>
                        <l>Contagious blastments are most imminent.</l>
                        <l>Be wary, then; best safety lies in fear.</l>
                        <l>Youth to itself rebels, though none else near.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="b7n5q3x8r4_spa" corresp="#b7n5q3x8r4_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>La doncella más recatada se prodiga bastante</l>
                        <l>si muestra su hermosura a la luna.</l>
                        <l>Ni la virtud misma escapa a golpes de calumnia.</l>
                        <l>El gusano hiere los brotes de la primavera</l>
                        <l>con frecuencia antes de abrirse,</l>
                        <l>y en la aurora húmeda de la juventud</l>
                        <l>los aires contagiosos son más inminentes.</l>
                        <l>Sé cauta, entonces; la mejor seguridad está en el temor.</l>
                        <l>La juventud contra sí misma se rebela, aunque nadie más esté cerca.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="z3m8f2k9h6_eng" corresp="#z3m8f2k9h6_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>I shall the effect of this good lesson keep</l>
                        <l>As watchman to my heart. But, good my brother,</l>
                        <l>Do not, as some ungracious pastors do,</l>
                        <l>Show me the steep and thorny way to heaven</l>
                        <l>
                            <app>
                            <lem>Whiles</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">whilst</rdg>
                            </app>
                            , a puffed and reckless libertine,</l>
                        <l>Himself the primrose path of dalliance treads,</l>
                        <l>And recks not his own rede.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="z3m8f2k9h6_spa" corresp="#z3m8f2k9h6_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>Guardaré el efecto de esta buena lección</l>
                        <l>como centinela de mi corazón. Pero, buen hermano,</l>
                        <l>no hagas como algunos pastores indignos:</l>
                        <l>muestran el camino escarpado y espinoso al cielo,</l>
                        <l>mientras, libertinos hinchados e imprudentes,</l>
                        <l>ellos mismos hollan el sendero florido del placer</l>
                        <l>y no se preocupan de su propio consejo.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <stage xml:lang="eng" xml:id="n6r4k2m7v3_eng" corresp="#n6r4k2m7v3_spa">
                        <app>
                        <lem>[Enter Polonius.]</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-absent"></rdg>
                        </app>
                    </stage>
                    <stage xml:lang="spa" xml:id="n6r4k2m7v3_spa" corresp="#n6r4k2m7v3_eng">[Entra Polonio]</stage>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="c7m2v9x4p1_eng" corresp="#c7m2v9x4p1_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Oh, fear me not.</l>
                        <app>
                        <lem n="."></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-present">[Enter Polonius]</rdg>
                        </app>
                        <l>I stay too long. But here my father comes.</l>
                        <l>A double blessing is a double grace;</l>
                        <l>Occasion smiles upon a second leave.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="c7m2v9x4p1_spa" corresp="#c7m2v9x4p1_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Oh, no temas de mí.</l>
                        <l>Me he quedado demasiado. Aquí viene mi padre.</l>
                        <l>Una doble bendición es doble gracia;</l>
                        <l>la ocasión sonríe a una segunda despedida.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="j5q8k2n6r4_eng" corresp="#j5q8k2n6r4_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>Yet here, Laertes? Aboard, aboard, for shame!</l>
                        <l>The wind sits in the shoulder of your sail,</l>
                        <l>And you are stayed for. There, my blessing with 
                            <app>
                            <lem>thee</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">you</rdg>
                            </app>
                            ,</l>
                        <l>And these few precepts in thy memory</l>
                        <l>
                            <app>
                            <lem>Look</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">See</rdg>
                            </app> 
                        thou character. Give thy thoughts no tongue,</l>
                        <l>Nor any unproportioned thought his act.</l>
                        <l>Be thou familiar, but by no means vulgar.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="j5q8k2n6r4_spa" corresp="#j5q8k2n6r4_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>¿Todavía aquí, Laertes? ¡A bordo, a bordo, por vergüenza!</l>
                        <l>El viento se posa en el hombro de tu vela,</l>
                        <l>y te esperan. Aquí, mi bendición contigo,</l>
                        <l>y estos pocos preceptos guarda en la memoria:</l>
                        <l>Guarda carácter. No des a tus pensamientos inmediata lengua,</l>
                        <l>ni a ideas desproporcionadas acción.</l>
                        <l>Sé afable, pero de ningún modo vulgar.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="v6b3p9m2x8_eng" corresp="#v6b3p9m2x8_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>
                            <app>
                            <lem>Those</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">The</rdg>
                            </app> friends thou hast, and their adoption tried,</l>
                        <l>Grapple them 
                            <app>
                            <lem>unto</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">to</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            thy soul with hoops of steel,</l>
                        <l>But do not dull thy palm with entertainment</l>
                        <l>Of each 
                            <app>
                            <lem>new-hatched</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">unhatch't</rdg>
                            </app>
                            , unfledged courage. Beware</l>
                        <l>Of entrance to a quarrel, but, being in,</l>
                        <l>Bear't that th'opposèd may beware of thee.</l>
                        <l>Give every man 
                            <app>
                            <lem>thy</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">thine</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            ear, but few thy voice.</l>
                        <l>Take each man's censure, but reserve thy judgment.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="v6b3p9m2x8_spa" corresp="#v6b3p9m2x8_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>Esos amigos tuyos, y su lealtad probada,</l>
                        <l>átales a tu alma con aros de acero,</l>
                        <l>pero no desgastes tu palma recibiendo</l>
                        <l>cada nuevo valor sin alas que nace. Guárdate</l>
                        <l>de entrar en riñas, pero si entras,</l>
                        <l>hazlo de manera que el contrario tema de ti.</l>
                        <l>Presta tu oído a todos, pero tu voz a pocos.</l>
                        <l>Toma el juicio de cada hombre, pero reserva el tuyo.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="x9k1c3m7v5_eng" corresp="#x9k1c3m7v5_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>Costly thy habit as thy purse can buy,</l>
                        <l>But not expressed in fancy—rich, not gaudy,</l>
                        <l>For the apparel oft proclaims the man,</l>
                        <l>And they in France of the best rank and station</l>
                        <l>Are of a most select and generous, chief in that.</l>
                        <l>Neither a borrower nor a lender, 
                            <app>
                            <lem>boy</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">be</rdg>
                            </app>
                            ,</l>
                        <l>For 
                            <app>
                            <lem>love</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">lone</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            oft loses both itself and friend,</l>
                        <l>And borrowing dulleth edge of husbandry.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="x9k1c3m7v5_spa" corresp="#x9k1c3m7v5_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>Tu vestido, tan costoso como lo permita tu bolsa,</l>
                        <l>mas sin mostrar fantasía: rico, no ostentoso,</l>
                        <l>pues el hábito a menudo proclama al hombre,</l>
                        <l>y en Francia los de más alto rango y estado</l>
                        <l>son en esto los más selectos y generosos.</l>
                        <l>Ni prestatario ni prestamista seas, hijo:</l>
                        <l>pues el préstamo suele perder tanto el dinero como al amigo,</l>
                        <l>y el pedir prestado embota el filo de la economía.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="t2r8m9k6b3_eng" corresp="#t2r8m9k6b3_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>This above all
                            <app>
                            <lem>:</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-orthography">;</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            to thine own self be true,</l>
                        <l>And it must follow as the night the day</l>
                        <l>Thou canst not then be false to any man.</l>
                        <l>Farewell. My blessing season this in thee!</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="t2r8m9k6b3_spa" corresp="#t2r8m9k6b3_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>Y, por encima de todo: sé fiel a ti mismo,</l>
                        <l>y se seguirá, como la noche al día,</l>
                        <l>que no podrás ser falso con ningún hombre.</l>
                        <l>Hasta pronto. ¡Que mi bendición madure en ti!</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="l9f4q2m7x5_eng" corresp="#l9f4q2m7x5_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Most humbly do I take my leave, my lord.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="l9f4q2m7x5_spa" corresp="#l9f4q2m7x5_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Con toda humildad me despido, mi señor.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="r8n6k4v3p2_eng" corresp="#r8n6k4v3p2_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>The time invests you. Go
                            <app>
                            <lem>.</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-orthography">,</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            Your servants tend.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="r8n6k4v3p2_spa" corresp="#r8n6k4v3p2_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>El tiempo te reclama. Ve. Te esperan tus sirvientes.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="f3v7b2m9k1_eng" corresp="#f3v7b2m9k1_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Farewell, Ophelia, and remember well</l>
                        <l>What I have said to you.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="f3v7b2m9k1_spa" corresp="#f3v7b2m9k1_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Hasta pronto, Ofelia, y recuerda bien</l>
                        <l>Aquello que te he dicho.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="m2x9k3v7b5_eng" corresp="#m2x9k3v7b5_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>'Tis in my memory locked,</l>
                        <l>And you yourself shall keep the key of it.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="m2x9k3v7b5_spa" corresp="#m2x9k3v7b5_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>Esta es mi memoria sellada,</l>
                        <l>Y tú mismo has de poseer su llave.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="q4k6m9b2x7_eng" corresp="#q4k6m9b2x7_spa">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Farewell.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#laertes" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="q4k6m9b2x7_spa" corresp="#q4k6m9b2x7_eng">
                        <speaker>Laertes</speaker>
                        <l>Hasta pronto.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <stage xml:lang="eng" xml:id="k7r2m4b9x3_eng" corresp="#k7r2m4b9x3_spa">[Exit Laertes.]</stage>
                    <stage xml:lang="spa" xml:id="k7r2m4b9x3_spa" corresp="#k7r2m4b9x3_eng">[Sale Laertes]</stage>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="d8m3v9k1r5_eng" corresp="#d8m3v9k1r5_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>What is't, Ophelia, he hath said to you?</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="d8m3v9k1r5_spa" corresp="#d8m3v9k1r5_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>¿Qué fue, Ofelia, lo que él te ha dicho?</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="k3v7x9m2b4_eng" corresp="#k3v7x9m2b4_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>So please you, something touching the Lord Hamlet.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="k3v7x9m2b4_spa" corresp="#k3v7x9m2b4_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>A tu merced, algo referente al Señor Hamlet.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="n9b2m5k7x3_eng" corresp="#n9b2m5k7x3_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>Marry, well bethought.</l>
                        <l>'Tis told me he hath very oft of late</l>
                        <l>Given private time to you, and you yourself</l>
                        <l>Have of your audience been most free and bounteous.</l>
                        <l>If it be so—as so 'tis put on me,</l>
                        <l>And that in way of caution—I must tell you</l>
                        <l>You do not understand yourself so clearly</l>
                        <l>As it behooves my daughter and your honor.</l>
                        <l>What is between you? Give me up the truth.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="n9b2m5k7x3_spa" corresp="#n9b2m5k7x3_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>Pues, bien recordado.</l>
                        <l>Se me ha dicho que muy a menudo, últimamente,</l>
                        <l>te concede tiempo en privado, y que tú misma</l>
                        <l>has sido pródiga en escucharlo.</l>
                        <l>Si es así — lo que se me ha dicho,</l>
                        <l>y, que a manera de precaución — te debo decir</l>
                        <l>No te entiendes a ti misma muy claramente</l>
                        <l>ya que esto contienda a mi hija y su honor.</l>
                        <l>¿Qué hay entre ustedes? Cuéntame la verdad.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="h2m7k4v9x3_eng" corresp="#h2m7k4v9x3_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>He hath, my lord, of late made many tenders</l>
                        <l>Of his affection to me.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="h2m7k4v9x3_spa" corresp="#h2m7k4v9x3_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>Él, mi señor, muchas ofrendas ha dado</l>
                        <l>de su afecto por mí.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="x7b3k9m2r4_eng" corresp="#x7b3k9m2r4_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>Affection? Pooh, you speak like a green girl,</l>
                        <l>Unsifted in such perilous circumstance.</l>
                        <l>Do you believe his "tenders," as you call them?</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="x7b3k9m2r4_spa" corresp="#x7b3k9m2r4_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>¿Afecto? ¡Bah! Hablas como niña verde,</l>
                        <l>sin probar en tan peligrosas circunstancias.</l>
                        <l>¿Crees en esas “ofrendas”, como las llamas?</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="m8k1v3x9r2_eng" corresp="#m8k1v3x9r2_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>I do not know, my lord, what I should think.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="m8k1v3x9r2_spa" corresp="#m8k1v3x9r2_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>No sé, mi señor, qué es lo que he de pensar.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="r4v8k2m7x3_eng" corresp="#r4v8k2m7x3_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>Marry, I will teach you. Think yourself a baby</l>
                        <l>That you have ta'en 
                            <app>
                            <lem>these</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">his</rdg>
                            </app> tenders for true pay</l>
                        <l>Which are not sterling. Tender yourself more dearly,</l>
                        <l>Or—not to crack the wind of the poor phrase</l>
                        <l>
                            <app>
                            <lem>Wronging</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">Roaming</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            it thus—you'll tender me a fool.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="r4v8k2m7x3_spa" corresp="#r4v8k2m7x3_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>Pues, te enseñaré. Piensa en ti misma como una bebé</l>
                        <l>que ha tomado esas dádivas por pago verdadero,</l>
                        <l>cuando no son moneda legítima. Trátate más alto,</l>
                        <l>o —sin cambiar el ritmo de esta pobre frase—</l>
                        <l>si fallas de esta manera — me harás tratar como un necio.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="b6m9v2k3x7_eng" corresp="#b6m9v2k3x7_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>My lord, he hath importuned me with love</l>
                        <l>In honorable fashion.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="b6m9v2k3x7_spa" corresp="#b6m9v2k3x7_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>Mi señor, me ha importunado con amor</l>
                        <l>en forma honorable.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="f9k7m2v4x3_eng" corresp="#f9k7m2v4x3_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>Ay, fashion you may call it. Go to, go to.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="f9k7m2v4x3_spa" corresp="#f9k7m2v4x3_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>Sí, honorable lo llamas. Anda, anda.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="k2v8x3m9r5_eng" corresp="#k2v8x3m9r5_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>And hath given countenance to his speech,</l>
                        <l>My lord, with almost all the 
                            <app>
                            <lem>holy</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-absent"></rdg>
                            </app> 
                            vows of heaven.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="k2v8x3m9r5_spa" corresp="#k2v8x3m9r5_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>Y ha confirmado su palabra,</l>
                        <l>mi señor, con casi todos los santos votos del cielo.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="x3m7k9v2b4_eng" corresp="#x3m7k9v2b4_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>Ay, springs to catch woodcocks. I do know</l>
                        <l>When the blood burns, how prodigal the soul</l>
                        <l>
                            <app>
                            <lem>Lends</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">Gives</rdg>
                            </app>
                            the tongue vows. These blazes, daughter,</l>
                        <l>Giving more light than heat, extinct in both</l>
                        <l>Even in their promise as it is a-making,</l>
                        <l>You must not take for fire. From this time
                            <app>
                            <lem n="time"></lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1" type="variation-present">Daughter</rdg>
                            </app>
                        </l>
                        <l>Be something scanter of your maiden presence.</l>
                        <l>Set your entreatments at a higher rate</l>
                        <l>Than a command to parle.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="x3m7k9v2b4_spa" corresp="#x3m7k9v2b4_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>Sí, trampas para atrapar becadas. Sé bien cómo,</l>
                        <l>cuando la sangre arde, cómo el alma pródiga</l>
                        <l>presta a la lengua promesas. Esos fuegos, hija,</l>
                        <l>dan más luz que calor; y se extinguen en ambos</l>
                        <l>aun mientras se forman las promesas.</l>
                        <l>No los tomes por llamas verdaderas. Desde ahora</l>
                        <l>sé más escasa en tu presencia de damisela.</l>
                        <l>Pon precio más alto a tus favores</l>
                        <l>que no ceder a cualquier ruego.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="m9v2k4x3b7_eng" corresp="#m9v2k4x3b7_spa">
                        <speaker>Polonius</speaker>
                        <l>For Lord Hamlet,</l>
                        <l>Believe so much in him that he is young,</l>
                        <l>And with a larger tether may he walk</l>
                        <l>Than may be given you. In few, Ophelia,</l>
                        <l>Do not believe his vows, for they are brokers</l>
                        <l>Not of 
                            <app>
                            <lem>that dye</lem>
                            <rdg wit="#F1">the eye</rdg>
                            </app> 
                            which their investments show,</l>
                        <l>But mere implorators of unholy suits</l>
                        <l>Breathing like sanctified and pious bonds</l>
                        <l>The better to beguile. This is for all:</l>
                        <l>I would not, in plain terms, from this time forth</l>
                        <l>Have you so slander any moment leisure</l>
                        <l>As to give words or talk with the Lord Hamlet.</l>
                        <l>Look to't, I charge you. Come your ways.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#polonius" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="m9v2k4x3b7_spa" corresp="#m9v2k4x3b7_eng">
                        <speaker>Polonio</speaker>
                        <l>En cuanto al príncipe Hamlet,</l>
                        <l>cree tan solo que es joven,</l>
                        <l>y que le es dado un lazo más ancho</l>
                        <l>que el permitido a ti. En corto, Ofelia,</l>
                        <l>no creas sus promesas, que son quebradizas,</l>
                        <l>no tienen el tinte que sus esfuerzos aparentan,</l>
                        <l>no buscan sino súplicas impuras,</l>
                        <l>respirando como juramentos santos y devotos</l>
                        <l>para engañar mejor. Esto va para todos:</l>
                        <l>No dejaré, por ponerlo a secas, de ahora en adelante</l>
                        <l>que tengas tan ligeros tus momentos de descanso</l>
                        <l>para que hables o converses con el Señor Hamlet.</l>
                        <l>Míralo bien, te lo ordeno. Continúa tu camino.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="eng" xml:id="v5b3k2m9x4_eng" corresp="#v5b3k2m9x4_spa">
                        <speaker>Ophelia</speaker>
                        <l>I shall obey, my lord.</l>
                    </sp>
                    <sp who="#ophelia" xml:lang="spa" xml:id="v5b3k2m9x4_spa" corresp="#v5b3k2m9x4_eng">
                        <speaker>Ofelia</speaker>
                        <l>He de obedecer, mi señor.</l>
                    </sp>

                    <stage xml:lang="eng" xml:id="k9x3m2v7b5_eng" corresp="#k9x3m2v7b5_spa">[Exeunt.]</stage>
                    <stage xml:lang="spa" xml:id="k9x3m2v7b5_spa" corresp="#k9x3m2v7b5_eng">[Salen]</stage>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
